(vi)  prepare macroeconomic and financial monitoring reports (daily and weekly); 
(vii)  prepare macroeconomic reports on assigned Asian economies as inputs to OREI 
policy reports and publications; 
(viii)  provide data and editorial assistance to OREI working paper series and other 
OREI publications; 
(ix)  provide  logistical  and  coordination  support  to  OREI  seminar  series,  website 
promotion and other activities as requested by ADB staff;  
(x)  assist in capacity building exercises for policymakers in the region; and 
(xi)  provide other research and general administrative support as may be requested 
by the project leader and/or other TA members. 

8.  Website developer (1 position, national, 18 person-months). The website developer will 
help the project leader and/or other TA members expand, improve, and operate the ARIC 
website, and OREI website. The website developer will be working on a daily basis at the ADB 
headquarters and will report to the principal economic analyst, project leader, and/or other TA 
members. Under the supervision of the project leader and/or other TA members, the website 
developer will 
(i)  design  and  develop  navigational  tools  using  state-of-the-art  technologies  to 
improve user access across various content areas of the website; 
(ii)  build and maintain efficient content management systems to track and manage 
content, including text and graphics published on the website; 
(iii)  build highly interactive interfaces, geo-data mapper and charting components for 
the  macroeconomic  and  financial  indicators  database,  integration  indicators 
database, and comparative toolkit for free trade agreement (FTA) database; 
(iv)  develop a multimedia facility to manage image galleries, podcasts, and video 
feeds; 
(v)  implement a tracking system to track website statistics on user hits and visits; 
(vi)  conceptualize and execute designs for new uploads; and suggest modifications 
in page design; 
(vii)  analyze program specifications, design, and implement programs to generate 
links and web pages, and test and debug the programs; 
(viii)  maintain or modify programs to revise and update the content of the new website; 
(ix)  develop new concepts to simplify website updating procedures; 
(x)  update and check the entire database for errors; and manage the file structure of 
the entire website; 
(xi)  post daily updates on the development, and global websites; 
(xii)  prepare technical documentation for the designed website; 
(xiii)  conceptualize and develop CD brochures and portable database applications; 
(xiv)  conduct usability testing to evaluate and measure the website’s ease of use; and 
(xv)  provide other IT support as may be requested by the project leader and/or other 
TA members. 

9.  Multimedia  designer  and  developer (1 position, national, 18 person-months). The 
multimedia  designer  and  developer  will  help  the  project  leader  and/or  other  TA  members 
expand, improve, and operate the ARIC website by undertaking graphic design work of the web 
contents and subsites to be created. The expert will be working on a daily basis at the ADB 
headquarters and will report to the principal economic analyst, project leader and/or other TA 
members. Under the supervision of the project leader and/or other TA members, the multimedia 
designer and developer will 
(i)  conceptualize designs and develop front-end templates for websites and subsites; 
(ii)  manage and update static contents for the ARIC website and related subsites;

  Appendix 3  13 
(iii)  conceptualize and execute specified design including icons and thumbnails of 
new web pages and additional subsites; 
(iv)  carry out other tasks related to web graphical design as assigned by ADB staff; 
(v)  provide ARIC support on site uploads and editing support for all ARIC online or 
publication materials; 
(vi)  conceptualize and implement designs for ARIC and OREI promotional materials; 
(vii)  provide layout services to various ARIC documents and OREI publications; 
(viii)  coordinate  with  relevant  departments  to  ensure  graphic  design  work  of  the 
website is consistent with design guidelines followed in ADB; 
(ix)  provide photography and video production support, edit video materials, convert 
files to various formats, produce CD/DVD materials,  prepare cover design, and 
assist in reproduction requests;  
(x)  assist in ARIC local events; and 
(xi)  provide other publication support as may be requested by the project leader 
and/or other TA members. 

10.  System and database developer (1 position, national, 18 person-months). The system 
and database developer will help the project leader and/or other TA members expand, improve, 
and operate the ARIC website. The system and database developer will be working on a daily 
basis at the ADB headquarters and will report to the principal economic analyst, project leader 
and/or other TA members as may be directed. Under the supervision of the project leader 
and/or other TA members, the system and database developer will   
(i)  improve the content management system for the macroeconomic and financial 
indicators  database,  which  include:  generating  new  html  and  excel  outputs 
needed for reports and website uploads; and adding new functions in the front-
end website interface of the user-defined section of the database; 
(ii)  revise the content management system for the regional integration indicators 
database, which include: adding new functions to facilitate inputs of various types 
of  data  sets;  and  creating  new  outputs  needed  for  website  uploads  and 
researches; 
(iii)  maintain and upgrade the FTA database content management system, which 
includes: adding a user-defined interface and merging the FTA database with 
other database systems of the website; 
(iv)  assist in the supervision of database-related collaboration projects with other 
ADB departments and external stakeholders, which includes: scoping of data 
requirements and assisting in the conceptualization of IT plan and framework; 
(v)  conceptualize,  design,  and  implement  other  database-related  system 
requirements for the website, particularly for new content as may be determined 
by the ARIC team; 
(vi)  design and implement front-end web tools to enhance website functionality and 
presentation; 
(vii)  revise, enhance, and optimize database and content management systems for 
the ARIC macro database, RCI and FTA database, and new content databases 
as may be determined by the ARIC team; 
(viii)  prepare  technical  documentation  for  implemented  database  and  content 
management systems; 
(ix)  conduct and oversee usability testing for the ARIC website; and 
(x)  provide other IT support as may be requested by the project leader and/or other 
TA members.
